<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Responsive Readability</title>
  <style>
    /* Base (mobile-first) styles */
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin: 20px;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      color: #333;
    }

    h1, h2, p {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }

    /* Larger screens (600px and up) */
    @media (min-width: 600px) {
      body {
        font-size: 16px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Responsive Webpage</h1>
  <p>
    This is an example of a mobile-first responsive webpage that adjusts its font size for better readability.
  </p>
  <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
  <p>
    On smaller screens, text should be easy to read without zooming or horizontal scrolling. This layout uses media queries to ensure that.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
